-- JPMorgan unwinds Bear hedge fund positions
-- 
-- Wed Jun 20, 2007 5:42pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/20/us-bearstearns-merrilllynch-unwind-idUSN2030435720070620

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - JPMorgan Chase & Co. ( JPM.N ) has closed out of its positions with two hedge funds managed by Bear Stearns & Co. BSC.N, and does not plan to sell any Bear assets on the open market, a source familiar with the situation said. 

 JPMorgan Chase has no further involvement with the two hedge funds that reported big losses through April, the source said. JPMorgan Chase declined to comment. Bear Stearns was not immediately available to comment.